          <span class="used-strip-sub">Production-oriented defaults and clear operational hooks</span>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="feature-grid">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>Auto-invalidation</h3>
        <p>Tag-aware invalidation and dependency-friendly patterns so stale reads are the exception, not the rule.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>Multi-backend</h3>
        <p>Redis, Memcached, in-process memory, disk, and SQLite share one interface — swap stores without rewriting call sites.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>Fits async and sync</h3>
        <p>Use <code>await</code> in FastAPI, Starlette, Django async, and workers. For blocking code, <code>get_sync</code> / <code>set_sync</code> or <code>@cached</code> on a normal function.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>Resilience</h3>
        <p>Circuit breaker, retries, and stale-if-error style patterns to degrade gracefully under pressure.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>HTTP caching</h3>
        <p>Starlette ASGI middleware for ETag and Cache-Control — 304-friendly responses when you enable the <code>web</code> extra.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>Observability</h3>
        <p>Prometheus and StatsD hooks plus OpenTelemetry-friendly tracing for cache spans.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>Vector helpers</h3>
        <p>Optional similarity and vector workflows when your stack needs semantic-style cache keys.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">◇</div>
        <h3>CLI</h3>
        <p>Inspect keys, stats, and health from the terminal for debugging and on-call.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

